CADI.Common.LogicalTarget.JPEG2000.Parameters

Class CODParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • CADI.Common.LogicalTarget.JPEG2000.Parameters.CODParameters

  • public class CODParameters
extends java.lang.Object
    This class storages the coding style default (COD) and the coding style component (COC). Further and detailed information, see ISO/IEC 15444-1 section A.6.1 and section A.6.2, respectively.
    Version:
    1.0 2008/11/07
    Author:
    Group on Interactive Coding of Images (GICI)

    • Field Detail

      • progressionOrder

        public int progressionOrder
        Progression order used to save the file.

        Valid values are:

        • 0- LRCP Layer-Resolution-Component-Position
        • 1- RLCP Resolution-Layer-Component-Position
        • 2- RPCL Resolution-Position-Component-Layer
        • 3- PCRL Position-Component-Resolution-Layer
        • 4- CPRL Component-Position-Resolution-Layer

      • numLayers

        public int numLayers
        Number of layers that the final codestream contains.

        Only positive values allowed.

      • multiComponentTransform

        public int multiComponentTransform
        Multiple component transformation. Allowed values are:

        Valid values are:

        • 0 - No multiple component transformation
        • 1 - Component transformation used on components 0, 1, and 2
        • 2 - Array-based
        • 4 - DWT-based
        • 3 - Array-based + DWT-based

      • WTLevels

        public int WTLevels
        DWT levels to applied.

        Negative values not allowed.

      • WTType

        public int WTType
        Discrete wavelet transform applied.

        Valid values are:

        • 0 - Nothing
        • 1 - Reversible 5/3 DWT
        • 2 - Irreversible 9/7 DWT

      • bypass

        public boolean bypass
        Style of code-block coding passes. Definition in MQDecoder. Further information, see ISO/IEC 15444-1 section A.6.1 (table A-19).

      • reset

        public boolean reset

      • restart

        public boolean restart

      • causal

        public boolean causal

      • erterm

        public boolean erterm

      • segmark

        public boolean segmark

      • blockHeight

        public int blockHeight
        Block height (exponent of 2).

        Values greater than 2.

      • blockWidth

        public int blockWidth
        Block width (exponent of 2).

        Values greater than 2.

      • precinctWidths

        public int[] precinctWidths
        Precinct width in the transformed domain for each and resolution level. Index means [rLevel] (rLevel==0 is the LL subband, and 1, 2, ... represents next starting with the little one).

        Values equal or greater than BlockWidth.

      • precinctHeights

        public int[] precinctHeights
        Same as resolutionPrecinctWidths but for precinct heights.

        Values equal or greater than blockHeight.

      • useSOP

        public boolean useSOP
        Use of start and end of packet headers.

        In both cases true indicates that the marker is used.

      • useEPH

        public boolean useEPH
